      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/cdc98d/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2023-09-26T06:09:26.771Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Alex asked before : would we need an \u201cHR structured mode\u201d.  I\u2019m still not convinced of that.  What I really like is : you start pedalling away, you have an idea in mind.  You do a warmup, put your HR target at what you want to do.  Do that for some time, then do something else and get back to HR to cool down.  I have a whole library of \u201cblocks of training\u201d, rather than full training sessions.  Like HIIT intervals and stuff like that.  I know : I should plan ahead, but hey, I\u2019m no pro rider.  I have a broad idea what I want to do and then I see how I feel <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>",
