      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/potsiea1/{size}/5703_2.png",
      "created_at": "2023-10-26T17:55:26.414Z",
      "cooked": "<p>It wasn\u2019t in a workout with intervals.</p>\n<p>It was in a workout with a structured ERG warmup (as HR warmup functionality doesn\u2019t work well for me), followed by a single steady state work interval. The plan was to switch control from ERG to HR at the end of the warmup.</p>\n<p>The feedback was that that transition resulted in a drop of resistance requiring significant manual adjustment, rather than being  a seemless transition.</p>",
